abstract: Earnings at the second-largest automaker in the world after Toyota remained dependent on the high-end Audi and Porsche brands.
snippet: Earnings at the second-largest automaker in the world after Toyota remained dependent on the high-end Audi and Porsche brands.
lead_paragraph: FRANKFURT — Volkswagen, Europe’s largest carmaker, said on Wednesday that net profit rose 19 percent in the first quarter as the auto market in Western Europe recovered.

headline.main: Volkswagen’s Net Profit Rises 19% Amid Recovery in Western Europe’s Car Market
